# Festag — popup header + body

Popups use a **large H1 title**, then a **T1 body sentence** directly underneath. Do **not** add a muted Zwischenüberschrift / second H1 line under the title.

## Do

```tsx
<h2 className="…-title">Client Panel</h2>
<div className="…-body">
  <p>
    Du bist im Client Portal. Für Entwickler-Zugang und Workspace-Tools
    wechsle zum Dev Panel.
  </p>
  {/* fields / actions */}
</div>
```

Reference sizes (AuthSecurityModal / AuthPanelSwitchModal / AuthRecoveryModal):

| Token | Desktop | Mobile (≤768) |
|---|---|---|
| **H1** title | `26px` / lh `1.28` | `28px` / lh `1.22` |
| **T1** body | `15.5px` / lh `1.65` | `16px` / lh `1.62` |

- **Light T1:** `#5c5c62` or `--fp-muted` on light surfaces
- **Dark T1:** `rgba(245,245,247,0.68)` or `--fp-muted`

## Don't

- Muted second H1 line under the title (`title-line--muted`, stacked subtitle)
- Small T0/eyebrow / kicker above or between H1 and T1
- Incomplete question fragments as the only body line
- Page `h1` leads on routes — those stay forbidden (`festag-no-page-leads`)

## Distinguish

| Surface | Under title |
|---|---|
| Page `h1` | **No** lead |
| Popup / sheet / modal | **Yes** — T1 full sentence, then fields/actions |
| Kickers | Still **no** |
| Middle dots in meta | Still **no** |
